                                Homeownership comes with its share of responsibilities, and one of the most important is maintaining your home. From routine maintenance tasks to unexpected repairs, the costs can add up quickly. To avoid financial stress, it’s essential to have a solid budget for home maintenance and repairs.
                            </p>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                In this article, we will guide you on how to budget for home maintenance and repairs, offering practical tips to help you plan for both expected and unforeseen expenses. By understanding how to allocate funds and prioritize projects, you’ll be better prepared to maintain your home without breaking the bank.
                            </p>
    
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Determine the Average Annual Maintenance Cost</h2>
                            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The first step in budgeting for home maintenance and repairs is to estimate the average annual maintenance cost of your home. Homeowners should expect to spend about 1-3% of the home’s value each year on maintenance and repairs.</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
